4. ING: PSD2-Compliant API System for Simplified Onboarding and Cross-Selling
ING, headquartered in the Netherlands, has developed an extensive PSD2-compliant API ecosystem that simplifies customer onboarding and drives cross-selling by offering aggregated account views. ING’s focus on reducing onboarding friction has led to more seamless customer experiences and increased uptake of cross-sold products.

PSD2-Compliant APIs: ING’s APIs adhere to the Revised Payment Services Directive (PSD2) regulations, which mandate secure and transparent data sharing between financial institutions and third-party providers. These APIs allow customers to connect all their financial accounts in one platform, enabling more efficient management of finances.
Multi-Bank Account Aggregation: ING’s aggregation API allows customers to view multiple accounts (even from different banks) in one place. This has enabled fintech partners like Yolt and Tink to offer customers a unified dashboard that tracks spending, saving, and income across all accounts.
API-Driven KYC: ING’s automated Know Your Customer (KYC) solution uses data collected through APIs to streamline onboarding processes. By automating identity verification, ING has reduced the time needed to onboard new customers, significantly decreasing drop-off rates.
Cross-Selling Services: ING uses customer data from its aggregation APIs to offer personalized cross-sell recommendations, such as investment products or insurance services. This has driven further engagement and cross-product sales.
